But perhaps the poor Dog has a mind to a Son and Heir, and to see himself growing up in a little Monkey-fac'd Representative; but, hark ye, my dear Friend Bell. take this saying of the Poet's along with you, and treasure it up;


Though Solomon with a thousand Wives,

To get a wise Successor, strives;

But one, and he a Fool, survives. Geddemme.

Besides the standing Pension, there must be an allowance too for Extraordinaries: for Example; 
                     •
                  or Balls at Court, and publick appearances of that kind. At such times, I say, the Courtiers will give themselves to the Devil for a little money, especially in hard times, when Salaries are ill paid.
